d.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
When we felt it was time to drag Callandre to epic-dom, we went to set up camp in SF. When we got there, we found that Jeaanie was camping him, and as we don't fight over spawns or camps usually, we decided to wait until the next go around. When the call to arms came for us to go help Jeaanie out, we all dropped everything and after a disastrous beginning (somone engaged before the troops were mustered) Ragefire was killed. Another guild (someone please help me out here) who people assumed was going to KS and take the Rage drop actually made Jeaanie's epic possible. There was a squabble about the other loot but it really isn't important to this discussion.<br>
<br>
After all the excitement died down, our whole guild settled in for the camp, claiming it, waiting for anyone to challenge, and to deal with it honorably if possible. I think Gruffnoy was wandering around at that time, but with not one person there to support him (glad to see you got your epic Gruff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) I am not sure if we started this process or if it had begun before, but we began simply by deciding that as a guild we would support our cleric in this endeavor. In the evenings we camped there, took shifts playing thru the nights. There was always many people there, except the wee hours, then just a group usually. <br>
<br>
Old friends came by, we hunted together, chatted, had a great time. I think this was where the Papaya Group was born <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Dahlea, a very dear friend of Calandre's spent nearly as much time there as we did. She did so because she wanted to support the effort we were making to keep a force in the zone to minimize the call to arms time. It was made up of people from many guilds at various times. <br>
<br>
When Rage popped, at around 11am PST, I was sleeping when the call came in. I logged on and within 10 minutes of Ragefire spawning, we had sufficient force amassed from all over the globe, from several guilds. This was because we had many people already there. As luck would have it, Gore had spawned in DL around the same time, so folks who may have come to challenge our claim were kept kinda busy and away from the rings hehe. <br>
<br>
We wanted to make everything as fair as possible for folks assisting, and also to avoid the scuffle that happened with the non cleric loot from the dragon, so that was handled first. Everything would be randomed. We had such a turnout, over 50 people who wanted to help, that we held off on engaging as long as we felt safe so that these people would get the chance to help us. For us it was a great bonding experience.<br>
<br>
After the dragon went down, rezzes and loot were handled, Dahlea took claim of the camp. She did as Callandre before her, and ooc'ed her claim, waiting for anyone to challenge, and had support there. I didn't go back more than twice because I was burned out from the week before, but I know that she did as we had done, and kept a guild force there, as well as friends to keep her company. <br>
<br>
My whole point in explaining how things kind of evolved is just to show why it worked. The show of a force there was important. A cleric there camping with a large show of support means a lot more than a cleric left to rot waiting for the damn human to spawn. I am glad that it has been kept alive, and yes, it does seem to be getting a bit skewed if people take the so called list too seriously. As has been so aptly stated in the previous pages, the order doesn't matter so much, it is the amount of time you put in, and it is between the clerics who are there to decide who might take priority the next go around. <br>
<br>
That being said, I need to comment on what Feadorn (sp?) has posted. I am a proponent of the current way the camp is being handled, no doubt of that, but if for some reason, the clerics there are not being given enough support as to have a reasonable number of people there already, thereby slowing the gathering of forces, then anyone is within their rights to bring in their own force and take care of the job. Yes, there should be a reasonable time frame, and it is up to those &quot;latecomers&quot; whether they wish to assist the current cleric or not. However, if this system is being observed as it began, getting the forces required to take down the dragon into the zone within several minutes shouldn't even be an issue, thereby rendering the point moot.<br>
<br>
To Salta, in my reference to getting your guild involved more in the support of your cleric, previous comments made me think that there was yet again a cleric left alone to claim the camp, something contrary to the effort currently being made, but that point was cleared up as erroneous for the most part, my apologies for any offense. I think it is great that so many of the larger guilds are helping out and I am sure that whatever squabbles are here on the board will not be so present in game. I think that for the most part, the way this camp is being handled and shared in by so many from so many different guilds can be a healing experience for so many injustices, real and supposed, that have made their way across these boards the past year. <br>
<br>
Regardless of what people say against things here, if the players of Quellious are participating and making this WORK, then nothing anyone can say will change that.<br>
<br>
