<br>
(1) Where in any of Sony's Big Steaming Pile of Horse Manure (forthwith BSPHM) does it state that kiting a mob doesn't make it yours? As far as I was aware any form of aggro from the mob to you makes it your mob, and nothing an individual GM has ever said can override that rule. The BSPHM states this, so where's this &quot;understanding&quot; about kiting come from? Hell, does this mean that if I'm wandering around CS with 4 Wyverns being stupid enough to follow me while I &quot;kite&quot; them, that anyone is within their rights to take them from me? Even if I haven't cast a nuke yet, and I'm still at the stage of rounding 4 of them up with snare? Because if that happened you can be damn sure the first thing I'd do would be to swear in /gu, and the second would be a petition.. And becuase of the BSPHM, as far as I'm aware the person taking the mob would be in deep doodoo.<br>
<br>
(2) Who decides what &quot;sufficient force&quot; is comprised of? Someone brought up the idea of 10 people attacking Rage. Would that comprise &quot;sufficient force&quot; in most people's eyes, since there is a minimalistic chance that they might succeed? What about 10 MB Wizards? Even better.. What if a band of 10 people decided to kite it simultaneously? Would that be considered a free mob or a claimed mob, by your understanding?<br>
<br>
Again, in all of the above cases, as far as the BSPHM is concerned once aggro is achieved the mob <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> claimed, unless they've changed it since I last fell asleep reading it. So even the people who are trying to use the rules to justify their attitude with this mob are very likely ignoring/breaking those very rules to suit their argument..<br>
<br>
Again, Verant/Sony have repeatedly stated that the written ruleset on their website is the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only canonical ruleset by which all EQ players must abide</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Therefore anything an individual GM has told people about the concept of kiting not counting as ownership of the mob is, as far as I can see, so much felgercarb.<br>
<br>
*shrug*<br>
<br>
Anyways, as I said.. I and Dragons of Saint George are still supporting the &quot;list&quot; and the people on it, as we welcome ANY effort to increase comradeship and friendship on Quellious.<br>
<br>
